🧠 The Idea Engine (Mutation × Frame × Selection)

This is a practical system for generating “good ideas” on demand.

Good idea = (memory mutation) × (frame fit) × (selection pressure pass)

⸻

⚙️ STEP 1 — Extract a Base Pattern (Memory)

Start with anything that works somewhere:
	•	business model
	•	biological system
	•	social behavior
	•	story / myth
	•	technology

👉 You’re not copying—you’re extracting the pattern

Example patterns:
	•	Feedback loop (TikTok algorithm)
	•	Scarcity signaling (luxury brands)
	•	Regeneration (axolotl 🦎)
	•	Network effects (social media)

⸻

🔄 STEP 2 — Mutate the Pattern

Now distort it on purpose.

Use these mutation operators:

1. Scale shift
	•	What if this worked at 10x / 0.1x?

2. Domain transfer
	•	What if this moved from biology → business?

3. Inversion
	•	What if we did the opposite?

4. Compression / expansion
	•	Can this be simplified or layered?

5. Timing shift
	•	What if it happens earlier / later?

⸻

👉 Example:
“Regeneration (biology)” →
→ “Business that rebuilds itself after failure automatically”

⸻

🧭 STEP 3 — Apply a Frame (Context Fit)

Now ask:

Where would this actually work?

Frames = environments with constraints:
	•	market (money)
	•	attention (social media)
	•	trust (relationships)
	•	time (fast vs slow systems)

⸻

👉 Same idea, different frame:
	•	Regeneration + healthcare → tissue repair
	•	Regeneration + finance → bankruptcy recovery system
	•	Regeneration + content → auto-reposting / remix engine

⸻

🔥 STEP 4 — Run Selection Pressure

This is where most ideas die (good).

Test against:

1. Reality
	•	Can this actually exist?

2. Incentives
	•	Why would anyone use/pay for it?

3. Simplicity
	•	Can people understand it fast?

4. Edge
	•	Is this better or just different?

⸻

👉 If it fails here → mutate again

⸻

🧪 STEP 5 — Compress to Action

Turn it into something executable:
	•	product
	•	system
	•	behavior
	•	experiment

If you can’t act on it → it’s not done.

⸻

